# TES Runtime Capabilities

This rule is TES-owned runtime capability, not project-owned governance. It may
be refreshed by the deterministic installer while `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`,
`CURSOR.md`, and previous project-owned Cursor rules are recovered from `.tes/bk/**`.

## TES Command Intents

Use these exact TES intents when the user asks for Tilly Engineering Skills:

- `/tes-init`
- `/tes-setup`
- `/tes-update`
- `/tes-align`
- `/tes-prospect`
- `/tes-mine`
- `/tes-open-obsidian`
- `/tes-cortex`
- `/tes-curate`
- `/tes-mcp`
- `/tes-field-reports`
- `/tes-doctor`
- `/tes-adapter`
- `/tes-bench`

Compatible aliases:

- `/tes:init`
- `/tes:update`
- `/tes:align`
- `/tes:prospect`
- `/tes:mine`
- `/tes:open-obsidian`
- `/tes:cortex`
- `/tes:mcp`
